<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Already-Connected on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/already-connected/</link><description>Recent content in Already-Connected on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/already-connected/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] C errno EISCONN — Already connected Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/errno-eisconn/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/errno-eisconn/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-errno-eisconn--already-connected-fix"&gt;[Solution] C errno EISCONN — Already connected Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When &lt;code&gt;connect()&lt;/code&gt; is called on a socket that is already connected, the call fails and sets &lt;code&gt;errno&lt;/code&gt; to &lt;code&gt;EISCONN&lt;/code&gt;. This error indicates the socket has already been connected to a remote endpoint.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Calling &lt;code&gt;connect()&lt;/code&gt; twice on the same socket without closing or disconnecting first.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The socket was connected via &lt;code&gt;connect()&lt;/code&gt; and then &lt;code&gt;connect()&lt;/code&gt; is called again with a different address.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A TCP socket that completed the three-way handshake is already in &lt;code&gt;ESTABLISHED&lt;/code&gt; state.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Programming error: failing to track connection state.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Check the socket&amp;rsquo;s connection state before calling &lt;code&gt;connect()&lt;/code&gt;. Use &lt;code&gt;getpeername()&lt;/code&gt; to verify existing connections.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C Socket is already connected: EISCONN</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/already-connected/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/already-connected/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="socket-is-already-connected-eisconn"&gt;Socket is already connected: EISCONN&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;EISCONN occurs when you try to &lt;code&gt;connect()&lt;/code&gt; a socket that is already connected, or when you use &lt;code&gt;sendto()&lt;/code&gt; on a connected TCP socket.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Double connect
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;connect&lt;/span&gt;(sock, (&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;struct&lt;/span&gt; sockaddr&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;addr, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;sizeof&lt;/span&gt;(addr)); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// first connect
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;connect&lt;/span&gt;(sock, (&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;struct&lt;/span&gt; sockaddr&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;addr2, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;sizeof&lt;/span&gt;(addr2)); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// EISCONN
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: sendto on connected socket
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Use send() instead for connected sockets
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: UDP connect then sendto
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;connect&lt;/span&gt;(sock, (&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;struct&lt;/span&gt; sockaddr&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;addr, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;sizeof&lt;/span&gt;(addr));
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;sendto&lt;/span&gt;(sock, data, len, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;, (&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;struct&lt;/span&gt; sockaddr&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;addr, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;sizeof&lt;/span&gt;(addr)); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// EISCONN
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-check-connection-status-first"&gt;Fix 1: Check connection status first&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;struct&lt;/span&gt; sockaddr_in peer;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;socklen_t&lt;/span&gt; len &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;sizeof&lt;/span&gt;(peer);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;getpeername&lt;/span&gt;(sock, (&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;struct&lt;/span&gt; sockaddr&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;peer, &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;len) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;==&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// already connected
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;} &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;connect&lt;/span&gt;(sock, (&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;struct&lt;/span&gt; sockaddr&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;addr, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;sizeof&lt;/span&gt;(addr));
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-use-send-for-connected-sockets"&gt;Fix 2: Use send() for connected sockets&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// After connect(), use send()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;send&lt;/span&gt;(sock, data, len, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// OK
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-use-sendto-for-unconnected-udp"&gt;Fix 3: Use sendto() for unconnected UDP&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Before connect(), use sendto()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;sendto&lt;/span&gt;(sock, data, len, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;, (&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;struct&lt;/span&gt; sockaddr&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;addr, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;sizeof&lt;/span&gt;(addr));
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/not-connected/"&gt;Not connected&lt;/a&gt; — ENOTCONN.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/connection-refused-c/"&gt;Connection refused&lt;/a&gt; — ECONNREFUSED.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/bad-file-descriptor/"&gt;Bad file descriptor&lt;/a&gt; — EBADF.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>